<subSubSection id="C305EAC06902FFD8FC98F95566C7FEA5" lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="110" pageId="19" pageNumber="109" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA0B94B6902FFDFFC98F9556418F80B" blockId="19.[151,1437,1534,2030]" pageId="19" pageNumber="109">
<emphasis id="B96B65596902FFDFFC98F955673EF917" bold="true" box="[199,308,1751,1777]" pageId="19" pageNumber="109">Remarks</emphasis>
: This species was described by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8EC4BA6902FFDFFEC5F9556567F917" author="Williamson, E. B." box="[666,877,1751,1777]" pageId="19" pageNumber="109" pagination="1 - 88" refId="ref12284" refString="Williamson, E. B. (1919) Results of the University of Michigan - Williamson expedition to Colombia, 1916 - 17. IV. Notes on species of the genus Heteragrion Selys with descriptions of new species (Odonata). Occasional Papers of the Museum of Zoology, University of Michigan, 68, 1 - 88. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 14454" type="journal article" year="1919">Williamson (1919)</bibRefCitation>
based on a series of 
<specimenCount id="9D1972C26902FFDFF80AF95562B3F917" box="[1109,1209,1751,1777]" pageId="19" pageNumber="109" type="male">33 males</specimenCount>
and 
<specimenCount id="9D1972C26902FFDFF8AFF9556360F917" box="[1264,1386,1751,1777]" pageId="19" pageNumber="109" type="female">17 females</specimenCount>
collected in a couple of weeks. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8EC4BA6902FFDFFD8EF97964A9F8F0" author="Bota-Sierra, C. A." box="[465,675,1787,1814]" pageId="19" pageNumber="109" pagination="49254663" refId="ref11343" refString="Bota-Sierra, C. A. (2016) Heteragrion peregrinum. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species, 2016, e. T 49254663 A 49256261. https: // doi. org / 10.2305 / IUCN. UK. 2016 - 1. RLTS. T 49254663 A 49256261. en" type="journal article" year="2016">Bota-Sierra (2016)</bibRefCitation>
catalogued it in the IUCN red list as Critically Endangered (CR) because, since its discovery by Williamson in 1917, it had not been found again. Despite of sampling efforts at the type locality and surrounding areas, where a large amount of its habitat had disappeared. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8EC4BA6902FFDFF86AF8C166E8F867" author="Bota-Sierra, C. A. &amp; Novelo-Gutierrez, R." pageId="19" pageNumber="109" pagination="553 - 571" refId="ref11240" refString="Bota-Sierra, C. A. &amp; Novelo-Gutierrez, R. (2017) The genus Heteragrion (Odonata: Zygoptera) in Northwestern Colombia, with the description of Heteragrion tatama sp. nov. Zootaxa, 4347 (3), 553 - 571. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4347.3.8" type="journal article" year="2017">Bota-Sierra &amp; Novelo-Gutiérrez (2017)</bibRefCitation>
presented images of color pattern of head and thoracic intersternites of 
<typeStatus id="54A407E96902FFDFF87FF8EA6281F864" box="[1056,1163,1896,1922]" pageId="19" pageNumber="109">paratypes</typeStatus>
deposited in Rosser W. Garrison personal collection (RWG). We rediscovered this species at new localities in 
<collectingRegion id="49DB77A96902FFDFF807F80962ABF843" box="[1112,1185,1931,1957]" country="Panama" name="Embera-Wounaan" pageId="19" pageNumber="109">Chocó</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="49DB77A96902FFDFF888F809634BF843" box="[1239,1345,1931,1957]" country="Colombia" name="Risaralda" pageId="19" pageNumber="109">Risaralda</collectingRegion>
Departments. Photographs of male cerci (
<figureCitation id="1324A5CE6902FFDFFE77F82D6472F82F" box="[552,632,1967,1993]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1940,1965]" captionTargetBox="[372,1216,930,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[363,1223,921,1921]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 11. Male cerci: H. peregrinum: Union Panamericana, Chocó (A) dorsal view (B) mediodorsal view (C) lateral view. Heteragrion tatama: PNN Tatamá, Risaralda (D) dorsal view (E) mediodorsal view (F) lateral view. Heteragrion valgum: Acandí, Chocó (G) dorsal view (H) mediodorsal view (I) lateral view. VbC: Ventro basal convexity." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253600/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="109">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
A–C), female intersternite, genital valves (
<figureCitation id="1324A5CE6902FFDFF83DF82D62B9F82F" box="[1122,1203,1966,1993]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1502,1527]" captionTargetBox="[386,1205,422,1464]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[376,1211,417,1482]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 15. Female structures: H. inca: Puerto Leguizamo, Putumayo (A) S9–10 lateral view (B) S9–10 ventral view (C) intersternite. Heteragrion m. mitratum: Puerto Berrio, Antioquia (D) S9–10 lateral view (E) S9–10 ventral view (F) intersternite (modified from Bota-Sierra &amp; Novelo-Gutierrez, 2017). Heteragrion peregrinum: Union Panamericana, Chocó (G) S9–10 lateral view (H) S9–10 ventral view (I) intersternite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253606/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="109">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
G–I) and head color pattern (
<figureCitation id="1324A5CE6902FFDFFCABF851673CF808" box="[244,310,2003,2030]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1533,1558]" captionTargetBox="[355,1230,681,1505]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[348,1240,669,1513]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Face color pattern: H. m. mitratum: (A) male Puerto Berrio,Antioquia (B) female Puerto Berrio,Antioquia. Heteragrion m. atroterminatum: (C) male Union Panamericana, Chocó. H. valgum: (D) male Acandí, Chocó. Heteragrion peregrinum: (E) male Union Panamericana, Chocó (F) female Union Panamericana, Chocó. Heteragrion tatama (G) male PNN Tatamá, Risaralda (H) female PNN Tatamá, Risaralda." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253596/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="109">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
E–F) are presented.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA0B94B6905FFD8FC98FF1B66C7FEA5" blockId="20.[151,1437,153,323]" pageId="20" pageNumber="110">
Color pattern of head of males is very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C1FC2C86905FFD8FEB8FF186594FF55" box="[743,926,154,179]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="20" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angustipenne">
<emphasis id="B96B65596905FFD8FEB8FF186594FF55" box="[743,926,154,179]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="110">H. angustipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because of the black postclypeus, but 
<taxonomicName id="4C1FC2C86905FFD8F913FF1866FEFF31" authorityName="Williamson" authorityYear="1919" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="20" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peregrinum">
<emphasis id="B96B65596905FFD8F913FF1866FEFF31" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="110">H. peregrinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs in having abdomen length close to 
<quantity id="4CE714AE6905FFD8FE90FF3E6513FF31" box="[719,793,188,215]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="20" pageNumber="110" unit="mm" value="35.0">35mm</quantity>
, while in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1FC2C86905FFD8FFDAFF3C6236FF31" box="[901,1084,190,215]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="20" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angustipenne">
<emphasis id="B96B65596905FFD8FFDAFF3C6236FF31" box="[901,1084,190,215]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="110">H. angustipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
abdomen is longer than 
<quantity id="4CE714AE6905FFD8F911FF3F6392FF31" box="[1358,1432,189,215]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.9" pageId="20" pageNumber="110" unit="mm" value="39.0">39mm</quantity>
, and the angle between medial process and tip of cerci is close to 90° in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1FC2C86905FFD8FFE7FF606265FF1D" box="[952,1135,226,251]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="20" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angustipenne">
<emphasis id="B96B65596905FFD8FFE7FF606265FF1D" box="[952,1135,226,251]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="110">H. angustipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="1324A5CE6905FFD8F820FF6362D3FF1D" box="[1151,1241,225,251]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1609,1634]" captionTargetBox="[347,1241,380,1588]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[347,1241,380,1588]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Male cerci: H. aequatoriale: San Luis, Antioquia (A) dorsal view (B) mediodorsal view (C) lateral view. Hetera- grion angustipenne: Mocoa, Putumayo (D) dorsal view (E) mediodorsal view (F) lateral view. Heteragrion bariai: Araracuara, Caquetá (G) dorsal view (H) mediodorsal view (I) lateral view. VbC: Ventro basal convexity." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3415713" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3415713/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="110">Fig. 7D</figureCitation>
), but close to 45° in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1FC2C86905FFD8FCEBFE846753FEF9" authorityName="Williamson" authorityYear="1919" box="[180,345,262,287]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="20" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peregrinum">
<emphasis id="B96B65596905FFD8FCEBFE846753FEF9" box="[180,345,262,287]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="110">H. peregrinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="1324A5CE6905FFD8FD37FE8767C5FEF9" box="[360,463,261,287]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1940,1965]" captionTargetBox="[372,1216,930,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[363,1223,921,1921]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 11. Male cerci: H. peregrinum: Union Panamericana, Chocó (A) dorsal view (B) mediodorsal view (C) lateral view. Heteragrion tatama: PNN Tatamá, Risaralda (D) dorsal view (E) mediodorsal view (F) lateral view. Heteragrion valgum: Acandí, Chocó (G) dorsal view (H) mediodorsal view (I) lateral view. VbC: Ventro basal convexity." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253600/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="110">Fig. 11A</figureCitation>
). Female is characterized by having an intersternite with a digitiform dorsal plate (
<figureCitation id="1324A5CE6905FFD8F930FE8766CAFEA5" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1502,1527]" captionTargetBox="[386,1205,422,1464]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[376,1211,417,1482]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 15. Female structures: H. inca: Puerto Leguizamo, Putumayo (A) S9–10 lateral view (B) S9–10 ventral view (C) intersternite. Heteragrion m. mitratum: Puerto Berrio, Antioquia (D) S9–10 lateral view (E) S9–10 ventral view (F) intersternite (modified from Bota-Sierra &amp; Novelo-Gutierrez, 2017). Heteragrion peregrinum: Union Panamericana, Chocó (G) S9–10 lateral view (H) S9–10 ventral view (I) intersternite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3253606/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="110">
Fig. 
<date id="FFA19F8B6905FFD8FCC8FEAA66CAFEA5" box="[151,192,296,323]" pageId="20" pageNumber="110" value="2015-01">15I</date>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
